 218:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****      (#) By default, after the @ref HAL_DCMIPP_Init and if the state is HAL_DCMIPP_STATE_RESET
 219:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          all callbacks are reset to the corresponding legacy weak (surcharged) functions:
 220:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          examples @ref PipeFrameEventCallback(), @ref PipeVsyncEventCallback()
 221:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          Exception done for MspInit and MspDeInit callbacks that are respectively
 222:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          reset to the legacy weak (surcharged) functions in the @ref HAL_DCMIPP_Init
 223:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          and @ref HAL_DCMIPP_DeInit only when these callbacks are null (not registered beforehand)
 224:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          If not, MspInit or MspDeInit are not null, the @ref HAL_DCMIPP_Init and @ref HAL_DCMIPP_De
 225:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          keep and use the user MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks (registered beforehand).
 226:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c **** 
 227:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          Callbacks can be registered/unregistered in READY state only.
 228:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          Exception done for MspInit/MspDeInit callbacks that can be registered/unregistered
 229:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          in READY or RESET state, thus registered (user) MspInit/DeInit callbacks can be used
 230:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          during the Init/DeInit.
 231:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          In that case first register the MspInit/MspDeInit user callbacks
 232:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          using @ref HAL_DCMIPP_RegisterCallback before calling @ref HAL_DCMIPP_DeInit
 233:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          or @ref HAL_DCMIPP_Init function.
 234:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c **** 
 235:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          When The compilation define USE_HAL_DCMIPP_REGISTER_CALLBACKS is set to 0 or
 236:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          not defined, the callback registering feature is not available
 237:../STM32Cube_FW_N6/Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_dcmipp.c ****          and weak (surcharged) callbacks are used.
